<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Import Device Emails - MobiControl</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="page">
    <div class="header-row">
      <div>
        <h1>Import Device &rarr; Email CSV</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Signed in as <%= username %></p>
      </div>
      <nav class="nav-links">
        <a href="/devices">All Devices</a>
        <a href="/groups">Device Groups</a>
        <a href="/logout">Sign out</a>
      </nav>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <% if (error) { %>
        <div class="error"><%= error %></div>
      <% } %>
      <% if (success) { %>
        <div class="success"><%= success %></div>
      <% } %>

      <form method="post" action="/devices/import" enctype="multipart/form-data">
        <label for="csvFile">CSV file</label>
        <input type="file" id="csvFile" name="csvFile" accept=".csv,text/csv" required>
        <button type="submit">Upload and import</button>
      </form>

      <p class="hint">
        On <a href="/devices">All Devices</a>, user email is read directly from each device's
        "User Email" custom attribute in MobiControl whenever it's set — no CSV needed for those
        devices. This import is only a <strong>fallback</strong> for devices that don't have that
        attribute set.
      </p>

      <p class="hint">
        The CSV needs two columns: a device identifier and the user's email. A header row with
        columns like <code>DeviceId</code>/<code>Udid</code> and <code>Email</code> is detected
        automatically; otherwise the first column is treated as the device ID and the second as
        the email. The device ID is matched against every ID-like field MobiControl returns for a
        device (Device ID, UDID, Serial Number, IMEI, etc.), so it doesn't need to match one exact
        field.
      </p>

      <% if (lastImport) { %>
        <p class="hint">
          Current mapping: <%= lastImport.mappedCount %> device(s) from "<%= lastImport.filename %>",
          imported <%= new Date(lastImport.importedAt).toLocaleString() %>. This resets on server
          restart/redeploy — re-upload the CSV if the mapping disappears from <a href="/devices">All Devices</a>.
        </p>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
